//Bio:

Let’s be honest. The bio of almost every dance music DJ / music producer / label owner reads the same. . . it starts by telling you how, “at an early age” they were influenced by the likes of their mother/father who were likely musicians. . . maybe they first learned of their musical talents singing in the shower, or their love for vinyl by raiding their folks record collection . . .
As a teen, maybe they started mixing hip-hop and landed a weekly residency at their mates’ house party. . . maybe after college they started promoting parties, learned producing tracks in Garage Band and launched a record label. . . next said producer puts out his first release on a mega trendy label and “hits the big leagues.” You get the point. . .
But then there are others who navigate their way into success via alternate routes. Maybe it’s not even about the “success” anyway. . .
Such is the tale of Danko Skystone, hailing from the placid environment in Melbourne, Australia, Danko’s dedication, humility, tireless work ethic and apt for quality, are all undoubtedly leading to his everlasting mainstay in the dance music sphere.

Instead of rehashing all his childhood accolades, let’s fast forward to the important stuff. . .

Danko possesses a distinct and skillful mixing style that is broadly described as House & Techno often giving a wink and nod to his Progressive background. As such, his reputation has lead him to play at some of the biggest clubs and festivals around the world such as Australia, Russia, U.S., Spain, New Zealand, and Japan. . .

His productions are best described as warm, deep, techy, forward pulsing and emotive. To which they have received applause and support by some of the world's elite level such as Hernan Cattaneo, Oliver Moldan, Stephane K, Max Graham, D-Nox & Beckers, Dubfire and Sandra Collins to name a few. In 2017, will see his first EP called “Oceania” on his new label Inversion Audio.
Presently he has just launched his own mixing and mastering company purely for the (rare) joy and satisfaction of helping others music and mixes to sound the very best possible. He is a master with DAW’s - ProTools, Cuebase, Ableton Live & Apple Logic.
Undoubtedly, Danko Skystone has always stood for balance and quality and long may it continue. . .

I thank all who support me so energetically!

I love making my own music.

The expressive themes that interest me typically pertain to human freedom in a post-modern world. Such themes include alienation, psychological repression, the existential vacuum, obsession, rage, absurdity, mourning, regret, neurosis, depression, death and the concept of self.  These themes may be bleak, yet all sounds are intended to be ultimately uplifting affirmations of human vitality and spirit.

Influences range from old-school industrial to musique concrète and contemporary classical, from kosmische musik to minimalism and dada, from power electronics to any form of genuinely experimental music.  While absorbing and acknowledging these influences, it is important to me to find and evolve my own sound.  

Besides making my own music, my major interests are physics research, literature, psychology and gardening.

Kevin Marino came into the world in the heat of the summer, June of 1996. The heat would stay with him- from his birth in Woburn, Massachusetts through his days at Woburn High School. Traveling south in 2011, Kevin found himself in the hot climate of Melbourne, Florida. It wasn't long before he made his way back to the New England area, passing Massachusetts and settling in Manchester, New Hampshire.
Before Kevin landed in Manchester, the burning desire to release his emotions and thoughts found its place on the form of poetry and journal-type recorded thoughts. His love for music- the connection to his soul and ability to remove himself from his troubles by letting the sounds and lyrics take him away- eventually combined with Kevin's poetic release, and an artist known as R.D.M. began finding a presence. He began writing rhymes and recording songs, developing his craft as a hip hop artist. Once in Manchester, R.D.M. established himself among the local emcees and caught the ear of Illitant, one of the area's most respected rhyme spitters. Illitant contacted R.D.M., explaining an idea of teaming with dedicated artists and how he enjoyed R.D.M.'s style, also noticing the potential R.D.M. possessed. Illitant offered to mentor R.D.M., and R.D.M. gladly accepted. This led to the formation of Synndicate Recordz under the management of Edward Lind.
R.D.M. knows real lyricism and poetry delivered with heart and conviction will emerge to dominance again in hip hop. He promises to keep those qualities in his music, and will help push Synndicate Recordz into recognition with music that has depth and lyricism that won't die as long as there's a desire burning within him.

I'm not your normal electro artist. I do use vocal effects, some that just may be a bit kæotic for you. I'm warning you, because I get that my style isn't exactly going to grab the attention of normal people.

Electro-Industrial artist. I started making music in late '04 and have been growing ever since into my own style. I don't do the generic rap, or pop. I compose the music and master it. I don't care for Hollywood, I make music because I have such a love for it. I've studied music in the sense of sound, and working with different styles. I've found the one I have the taste for of the genres I've worked with in the past, so that's the style I personally work with for the music I put out for y'all to hear. When it comes to helping others record, I have no problem working with whatever style the artists wants to make. I don't like writing with just one sound throughout my song like how a lot of songs now-a-days have. Songs have variation to them, not the same sound; or sample if you want to be real, playing over and over again. My songs will have a layout to them, and I won't just write random words over a track that has intro/verses/chorus's/bridge/outro. I know that's a style all these rappers like to do, but I'm not a rapper, so don't expect something that simple and untalented. My music has it's own variety and taste to it. If you like it, cool. Hate it, cool. Whichever rows your boat.

"Like some great prowling Sasquatch groping its way through the thin spaces between shelving stacks in an endless archive of musical interest WREKIT88 is a wonder of the internet. Not content to just put a “Singer Wanted” sign in their local music shop Welsh songwriters Chris and Neil have created this project as a way to reach out to vocalists all over the world, crossing genres and languages, collaborating remotely in a spirit of limit-pushing and simple enjoyment. Indeed there is a certain circuitous pleasure in this particular track since singer Van Wyck is a connection that came through this very website (via my fellow moderator Ludwig Janssen). After what has been a largely fraught few years politically such cross-border creative alliances are so valuable. This is what artists are supposed to do: connect – not just with audiences but with each other. Yet so many only build private temples to their own egos. Well done WREKIT88 for creating music in such a spirit of playfulness and togetherness." written by Louis Barabas, BBC Fresh on the net moderator....Thanks for that:)

Conjuro Nuclear is occult music, solo project formed by Emesis in 2012 and hailing from Barcelona, Spain. The ecclectic background blends a lo-fi, minimalist, hypnotic fusion of dark sounds, ranging from black punk, darkwave, synth music and psychedelia. Four works were released: " ♄ " (2016), "Reacciones Paganas" (2015), "Conjuro Nuclear" (2014) and "Luna llena y radiación (2013) ...

>> "Some may say this Spaniard can't make up his mind, I'd say he doesn't have to. Wicked stuff that makes me think about creepy dwarves playing in the mountains." << Hansel Mercher (Caligari Records) / Decibel Magazine. [The Man Behind Caligari Records Favorite Tapes of 2015] 

>> "The project by Spain’s CONJURO NUCLEAR is one of the most interesting things I have heard all year. He is one of the few artists that has been able to combine Deathrock and Black Metal, but make it sound rad! There is no way you will not be able to hear CONJURO NUCLEAR’s passion and conviction. What will stick in your mind is the sinister melodies you will encounter of this tape. Love you to follow there too, so I can hear some more of your music :-)

A Mini Biography: Music has been a part of my life since a young child (my whole family is musical, though of different styles, with my step-father's fantastic rock-band and analog synths, bass and acoustic guitar, my mother's gorgeous Irish folk-band, autoharp and dulcimer, my brother's beautiful self-taught guitar, and my Dad's famous banjo playing) :)   

At a young age of about 5, I attempted composing my own piano works whilst begging my mother for piano lessons; and after about a year, my wish became reality and I trained for the AMEB (Australian Musical Examination Board) exams. I eventually started performing live, with amateur tours around the country area for a singing group and for theatre groups (though that was a long time ago now!). 

But eventually, I headed down a different path in academia, in getting my Bachelors degree, Masters degree and a PhD.

Now I have a chance to find this dream again, slowly but surely, as long as its fun. I also find it very therapeutic, as music can often express so much more than words can. It is a journey where time seems to have no meaning. This is a 'musical diary' of sorts, as I struggle through a difficult time in life health-wise, ... my escape .... music :-)

So, I would love it if you would follow me on this 'journey' because any advice or feedback would be greatly appreciated :)

Of course, I am also here as a Fan, and would love to find more people to listen to! There are so many wonderful, talented, and often undiscovered musicians up here, and I cannot get enough of your music! I have very eclectic tastes in music. 

My apologies too if there is ever a delay in my replies, as I can't always be here, but will try to get back to you and comments, I appreciate them so much. Hoping to find all my friends, and new ones too! ;-)

Hi there folks, there's no doubt about it. I've got the Music bug! And, being an enthusiastic Student of Life, and a Passionate Improvisational Pianist &   Composer,  as far as I'm concerned, we should all hope to be infected by it! :)  Yes, it's all about 'Sharing the Joy, and connecting up with all of the amAzing 'Creatives' who bring it forth!  In fact,  the creativity and willingness 'to Engage' that i find here on SoundCloud quite simply Blows me Away! :) It's an ever-expanding Feast that nourishes and inspires on so many levels. 

Music Communicates the emotional and Informational content and context of Heart, Mind, Spirit, and Soul. And 'Letting it Flow' is where itz at as I hEAR iT! :) 

Over this past year or so since becoming part of the SoundCloud community, my Joy in, and Passion for Creative Musical Expression has  increased exponentially along with my appreciation of all the wonderfully passionate musicians and creatives world-wide who have devoted themselves to letting it take form. 

Here's a bit of a bio, if anyone is interested.  

Somehow my Muse got my attention at a tender age, about the time I was completing my Royal Conservatory training. My memory being poorer than most, I began improvising in the passages I had forgotten. And while the audience seemed unaware, my teacher chastised me indulgently, saying, "it appears I have a budding composer on my hands"!  And thus began my Odyssey into the wonderful Vibrational world of Sound!:-) In-deed, I have been an ardent, attentive and appreciative acolyte of my Muse ever since. 

During the early 1970s I had the pleasure and honour of a three year friendship and Master Class with the then Octogenarian Composer Manoah Leide-Tedesco , one of Tone Poem giant Richard Strauss` favorite pupils and friend of Maurice Ravel and other 20th century composers such as Stravinsky (whose music he helped popularize). Since then, whether Improvising, listening, studying composition or devoting myself wholly to the visual arts for years at a time, I have been deeply aware that sharing my musical insights , teaching, and or mentoring young aficionados came with the territory!   I love it, although I am afraid that as my consciousness expands...that I know less and less each year! :-)  

The Tonal Oasis called SoundCloud is a fine and wondrous place in oh so many ways.  And with your support and appreciation, I de-Light to share my music with an ever widening audience. I call what i upload ' Sound-Seeds'.  Most of these 'bed tracks' call out to be fleshed out by passionate soloists who somehow Resonate with my Soundz and Ideas.  So please drop me a line, as i am most interested in letting them bear more fruit through collaboration, interpretation, re-mixing or use in other media.    

And on a personal Note, a Huge Thank-You to each and all who listen, inJoy, and Re-Post onwards what finds it's way thru me! :) Bless y'all.  It's my Joy to simply 'Let' the Creative Spirit find expression through this instrument of Body, Mind, and Heart!  I hope you will find some peace, joy, and rest, in at least some of my improvisations, compositions, or soundz. 

Insofar as playing, and composing  ... as you continue on in Your journey into  the infinite 'Cave of Wonders' we call Music, I wish you all the very best in all Your creative endeavours. 

So Be Kind to yourSelves and one another. Be Audacious, Ready to Play, and above all, share the Joy of being able to express whatever you're feeling. 

In-deed, may The Muse continue to 'Sing on and Play on' through each of us !   For this is one way this 'ol world is lifted up, and Changed for the better - note by note, and smile by smile .  

 Yes, may we simply Let our Creativity flow forth without concern for results.
                                   Peace

                                    Gary *+*

A moonbow (also known as a lunar rainbow or white rainbow), is a rainbow produced by moonlight rather than sunlight.
Moonbows are much fainter than solar rainbows, due to the smaller amount of light reflected from the surface of the moon. Because the light is usually too faint to excite the cone color receptors in human eyes, it is difficult for the human eye to discern colors in a moonbow. As a result, a moonbow often appears to be white.[1] However, the colors in a moonbow do appear in long exposure photographs. (Source: Wikipedia: Moonbow)

I’ve never ever believed that I will get a poet. 
I tried to write some criminal stories and a lot of music tracks but no poems.
My rebirth 24th of July 2010 changed everything in my brain, my soul, my spirit and in my heart.
This is the (short) story of my rebirth:

I’ve been driven home after a session with my psychologist talking with her about my fears and my anxiety. I was waiting for the lights getting green. The lights changed on green and I wanted to start my car when I felt something inside of me. I was surprised and hesitated. Then I started my car. Suddenly a huge van crossed my way. The van had a very high speed and would have crashed me in total at my driver side if I would have started fast. After that I felt HIM, our Lord, inside on my body, inside my heart and it was a very nice warm feeling. No anxiety, no fear at all. This was my rebirth in July 2010.

My rebirth changed everything in my life so I started writing, first alone then with composing music tracks.
All poems are written to express my emotions I have in my life. There are lots of emotions.
I want to say “Thank you God” with all of my work cause he let me to silence and tranquillity (although I need more of this but I’m still praying, lol).
I’m not a thinker. You will read and experience. 
I’m more a feeler of his love and his words. 
Some tell me I´m a very good feeler but I´m not gifted or talented of my own. I’ve got that gift from him to serve him and to follow his way. Nothing else I believe.
Sometimes it’s hard to put his feelings I perceive into words so you, my dear reader, can perceive and feel them too. 
I try hard to express my feelings in a way you can understand. 
I try hard to express my feelings in a way they’ve worked inside of me.
I’m on his way but his way is a hard way.
He leads me and I will follow till the end of my time.

It's been a long road, but I now have a label- Creative Commons- to work with as far as I know. 

I have been writing songs since 1964,
My first was "Ode to JFK".
I didn't have any way to publish it and never did.
It is long since lost.
I have tried to write to match old classical styles or have the songs be able to be done by an orchestra or symphony.
The Beatles songs can be performed by orchestra or symphony.

I have CDs of songs of artists back to the old classics of earlier centuries.

The CDs are of Frank Sinatra, Bing Crosby, Gene Autry, Roy Rogers, and Billie Holliday, She is on a CD with others.

The CDs include Shania Twain, Dean Martin, Reba McIntyre and many more.

My song - Demummified- is about a situation which was almost cartoonish for me, but I couldn't, or at least didn't convey that fact in the song.

I was working three jobs after serving as daddy to a friend's son.   He was in the service at that time.

I always liked to eat and unwind after work before going to bed. 

A new cafe had opened up on my route to home and I stopped to eat.  

I was so tired that I was almost asleep while waiting for my food.

The young server came over and started talking to me and initially I thought I must have been in a cartoon.    At that time I wondered if I somehow had gotten into a cartoon about a drunk who thought he saw dancing girls.

I quickly woke up enough to realize that the server was talking to me and asking me if I could stay with her at work all night.   She was just 16 and on her first job.   

I had a lot of sympathy for her situation, but knew  that I couldn't spend the night because I had to go home and get a couple of hours of rest before going to my day job.

I did eat at the new place about twice a week after work and the server and I talked about everything and nothing.

The song describes the amazing effect she had on me; perhaps because of my sympathy for her.    I had thought I was as good as dead and couldn't have feelings.

For me it was a Disneyesque situation and I thought it was worthy of a song and perhaps a comedy show with Fred Murray or someone from Disney to bring out the comedy.

The experience is almost impossible to explain.

Thanks for reading this and visiting my page.I have a pretty wide selection of styles and genres that I work in, so if you don't like the first track or 2 you hear, give a few more a try and I imagine you'll find something of value in the pile.I always appreciate your thoughts on my music, so please feel free to leave comments. I also accept any kinds of feedback/critique, my art grows better and stronger from it.If you ask me to comment on your track (that is unreleased), be ready for the possibility of 'feedback' - not ego-stroking.I'm not attacking you or trying to embarrass you.I'm seriously trying to help your mix/song reach another level, so if you have thin skin about your art/track/music, you may not want to directly ask me to listen/comment. That said, keep in mind it's based entirely on my opinion/experience only, and that's really not worth that much, but I thought it was fair to say this as a few people have gotten offended when I didn't just put "great track" in their timed comments. Honestly, most of the time I only mention what I really like or make mix suggestions, I can see the beauty in everyone's self expression.

Btw, the term "WIP" means it is a work in progress.  These are the developing tracks that I can use feedback on the most.  
p.s. If you should want a a mp3 of anything, just ask. Don't rip a lousy copy when you can easily get a hi-res version.
As Always, thanks for listening.

Hello! My name is Hans Henning Thomas. I think, I´m more a soundengineer than a songwriter and more a songwriter than really a singer/musician. I started to play guitar  late, i.e. on the age of sixteen and had never learned an instrument before. So my first musical influences have been by songwriters, because I firstly payed most of my attention to the lyrics. My musical understanding developed at this time, moving away from home and hanging around with some friends. At this time I did my first steps by grounding a band. But we were influenced more by the era of such as the Doors, Rory Gallagher, Neil Young, Jimmy Hendrix,  Pink Floyd or the first Deep Purple cast, - while the actual successful music at this time sadly was New German Wave and the like.

Later, after becoming an firstly unemployed physics, I followed my intention and turned my passion to trade, becoming a sound engineer. After all I got a well paid job in an public supported analog sound studio for a decade, recording and teaching some people in sound engineering. Some of my songs, published here, are a result from this era.

Now I´m working again as a physics / engineer, and music became my fervour again. In my life I lived in many different towns, in East and West Germany -  i.e. Düsseldorf, Braunschweig, Paderborn, Berlin, (1/2 year Tropea, Calabria, Italy), Hagen Westf, Siegburg, Dresden (Neustadt) and now I turned to Rahden, Westf., again, where I live deep in the country in an integral nature reserve. The experiences, I got and the people I met, might be an insperation for my philosophy and my music.

Thanks to the new computer technologies, I was able to build myself a modern home recording studio again, to produce my own and my friends music in a good quality.

My intention for the next time is, to listen to the theme and sound of the nature and turn it to music. The Intro of my song "Wild Ducks Flying" ("Flieg mit dem Wind") is a good example for this project. It came up to me, when I recorded some wild ducks trough my open window, flying over my house. I loaded the samples into a software synthesizer and started to made music to it, leaning on the style of some early Pink Floyd projects. This song should be regarded to migrant birds in analogy to the human society, nowadays.

I plan to go on this way in my next holiday, at least for a month, recording and using the sounds of a forest at night and the like. 

I hope you like and enjoy at least some of my songs :-)

I am fundamentally an electronic, ambient and soundscape artist. I occasionally challenge myself to do beats but it’s more the exception rather than the rule and a bit outside of my comfort zone. I like sonic landscapes that captivate the listener and take them to unknown places. I remember discovering Eno’s Ambient albums and finding myself admiring their ability to be both background and foreground depending on mood. Their ability to create a space to drift with one’s thoughts was revolutionary for me.

From an artistic standpoint - this is one of the most important quotes I've ever come across and it totally applies to music:

"Children are capable, of course, of literary belief, when the story-maker's art is good enough to produce it. That state of mind has been called "willing suspension of disbelief." But this does not seem to me a good description of what happens. What really happens is that the story-maker proves a successful "sub-creator." He makes a Secondary World which your mind can enter. Inside it, what he relates is "true": it accords with the laws of that world. You therefore believe it, while you are, as it were, inside. The moment disbelief arises, the spell is broken; the magic, or rather art, has failed. You are then out in the Primary World again, looking at the little abortive Secondary World from outside. If you are obliged, by kindliness or circumstance, to stay, then disbelief must be suspended (or stifled), otherwise listening and looking would become intolerable. But this suspension of disbelief is a substitute for the genuine thing, a subterfuge we use when condescending to games or make-believe, or when trying ... to find what virtue we can in the work of an art that has for us failed."
-- J. R. R. Tolkien

My goal as a musician is to try to build and maintain Tolkien’s so-called secondary world. It is predicated on my bias that music should be enjoyable to listen to. Things that are too out in the edges become academic. Interesting in their own right but only (truly) successful if immersive. Once the listener is immersed in this secondary world my aim is to keep them there in a suspended state and in the post-rock sense, blur the lines between genres and time periods to encourage a state of reverie.

Musically, when I discovered 70 and 80's electronic music there was no turning back. I'm often trying to take the listener into a story or narrative that blends the past with the present. As a result, there are frequent (and unabashed) musical references to seminal artists that have in effect lead me to this point. 

Big nods to Eno, Vangelis, Froese, Schultze, Jarre, Sylvian, Zukay, Popol Vuh, Mathias Grassow, Pink Floyd, The Orb, Steven Wilson, Bass Communion, Explosions in the Sky, Godspeed You! Black Emperor, and a host of others.

I also tend to do longer format "Slow Music" (think "slow food"). It’s not a conscious effort but sometimes the story the music wants to tell takes a little more time than the commonly prescribed "less than 7 minutes". Wave interactions for example can take a little while to really develop and can’t be rushed along – they need room. At any rate, I thank my listeners who are curious enough to stick with a long track or two and I hope you are rewarded for your time.

Lastly, I have an interesting and rewarding day-job which allows me the luxury of doing this for fun. Someday that may change, but right now the freedom to explore without hindrance or compromise is extremely compelling. Getting back to making music is something I've put off for many years longer than I should have. If this rings true for you as well, heed the call - life is short.
If you’ve dropped by and had a listen – Thanks! Please feel welcome to leave me a note or comment if you’re so inclined. I'm always interested in people's impressions and reflections.

Applex Twin( aka BettyApple )現場風格比風中奇緣還的狂暴感人，以摧毀新世界秩序的抽象聲學為概念LiveSet，僅靠一台筆電/塑料控制器/麥克風，佐Drone+Post Punk +Wonky Noise + Industrial+Techno音域食材，煲煮一道見不到卻撞得魂飛魄散之迷湯，灌進詭譎的宇宙氤語，簡直叫人淺嚐即失重幻入天際。

Applex Twin是藝術家Betty Apple化名。源於電子樂鬼才 Aphex Twin 睽違20年後發表電子樂創作新碟「SYRO」的辨別真偽事件：當時Youtube上眾多以Syro之名，實際上置入自己的創作的音樂的偽AphexTwin。BettyApple 乘勢以文字雙關 Applex Twin為其電音化名，祭出當代電子樂的擬像哲學，拜向90年代的臥室電音碼頭，也向21世紀的網路擬像世代致敬。
Applex Twin的音樂近年散錄於台灣獨立廠牌「派樂黛」，法國獨立廠牌Hormonal Vibrationz，受R&S Records旗下女皇「Paula Temple 」於Dummy Mag專訪中，欽點ApplexTwin 為2016年受啟發之女製作人之一，2017年於「Tsugi」Mag 2月號，Paula Temple 選輯混音發行。

Bio:
Conor’s songs are set in the working-class suburban Dublin of his formative years.  They depict everyday local characters as they negotiate life’s various pressures and challenges. Conor does not mind comparisons with Billy Bragg, Michael Head, Bruce Springsteen and their many disciples. But he will quip that none of those guys are from Clondalkin.   

Conor’s stories and themes could be pulled from the pages of an evening newspaper. He sings about railway stations, butcher shops and endless cups of tea.  His songs lack sentimentality and instead, they capture those small neighbourhood details that typically slip through the cracks. The whispered conversations at the pub about the couple whose marriage is floundering. Or the rumour about the wild kid who has found unlikely and fleeting calm in a new girlfriend.

Some bio from me: I'm a portuguese self taught guitar player with a passion for good music. I like all genres of music but the ones i find myself enjoying the most are tracks that have a bluesy, jazzy sound to it.
Growing up at from about age 6-10 i listened to a lot of grunge, nu metal and other genres but mostly nirvana, korn, limp bizkit, pearl jam, stone temple pilots, radiohead, the offspring and system of a down. From 10 to about 16 i listened to a lot of hip-hop and reggae music, mostly portuguese hip-hop bob marley and gentleman. 
It was only at 16 that i finally first picked up a guitar. I fell in love with it from the start, and as soon as i learned the first chords i knew i wanted to be a player. The moment for me that i said i want to do this was after looking up "Blues" on youtube and listening to a bb king solo. I was so amazed at what he could do with the guitar and the whole style he created that it completly blew my mind!
After i started playing guitar i started expanding my music taste to all diferent genres ranging from my guitar favorites like: jimi hendrix, b.b. king, led zeppelin, pink floyd, john mayer and dire straits to jazz/blues/rnb greatest: Frank sinatra, stevie wonder, miles davis, chet baker to totally different genres like Tool, The doors, sbtrkt, alt-j, tame impala, the xx, Manel Cruz, Linda martini, etc etc.

So this here is my little project, i trully love making tracks and posting them online for you guys to enjoy :)

I've been producing electronic Music since 1998,  Primarily focusing on Underground Techno, be it  DubTechno or 90's style IDM music, Most of my tracks are rather Chilled out Ambient but I also love to do more upbeat raw Techno.  I prefer more Abstract styles as opposed to Pop or dance music.  In my early days I made a lot of IDM,  Experimental,  Acid Techno.  Though at this point my sound is generally more Chilled out and Ambient.  I started making music at age 7 When I started piano lessons but by age 13 I Picked up guitar as well.  

I played guitar for along time and played in bands here and there but didn't really start to produce music until about 1997-99  When I got my hands on a copy of FL Studio.  
Thus my career in Music production using computers and Midi hardware began.  I have created over 400 Tracks since then lol.  

I wouldn't trade doing this for anything!  I never would have expected to have built such a large following here!  In the end I am also a listener and fan myself though. As well as being an avid Music collector and still believe in buying a Cd on occasion too ;)  

I have made so many friends here on the cloud and I will say this is the best Music community there is online period.  

I sincerely appreciate all comments and feedback!  I still can't believe the amazing support I have gotten on here.  I do seriously try and listen to as many fellow soundcloud artists Tracks as I can.  And If I don't get to yours Please don't hesitate to PM your work!  I love listening to Music what can I say it is my passion and has gotten me through so many difficult times in my life!  

I know that this is a community of artists and I am not here to Just promote my work.  This site is great for making friends and supporting some amazingly talented people as well.  Musicians that deserve to be noticed.  The amount of Talent on this site is just mind boggling and I do my best to support my friends here in the soundcloud community!

Enjoy the music and Keep making it too guys!

city: Founder Of Confusion In Motion Record Label
description:
Getting back in the studio now after months, just taking it one day at a time, and as always taking something positive from each day :)
In 2002 l was diagnosed with an Arnold Chiari Malformation and Syringomyelia which l was to go on and learn would have a big impact on both my mental and physical health. I also discovered as the years went by just how much of a 'Stigma' is attached to people with illnesses. At the end of the day we are still individuals and should not be labelled. We should be known for our artistic creativity first and most importantly, not 'that person with a illness or disability'. This is why i am setting up 'Project CODA' please follow the link below my bio for more information.

But my creative journey started back in the early 90’s when l produced #music, generally #house, #techno and #trance and some very #experimental forms of music.  I believed that the right music in the right environment could not only give you a natural euphoric high but could also be a form of distraction and escapism from the angst of the pressures life throws at us. In 1993 due to illness i had to give up everything in regards to music, apart from listening too and being a vinyl collector & addict.

Most of my time over the following years were spent learning coping mechanisms for pain and symptoms of the condition but in 2013/2014 l began setting up a small studio and l finally returned to producing music again in 2015.  I found this was the best coping mechanism of all even though the type of music l am now producing is a very different style to back then.  Music can take you to a different level but unfortunately the effects music can produce within the body and mind could never be given in tablet form.

I try not to let my disabilities rule my life and as difficult as it can be l try to take a positive from each day.  Life is about what we can do, however small, not what we can’t.

Music is my drug..........................

I would like to thank everyone for listening to, liking, commenting and reposting my music, i appreciate it :)

Bonjour et bienvenue sur ma page soundcloud !   
Je crée mes musiques avec les logiciels Ignite, ACID Xpress et ABLETON 9 Live Lite .Je ne suis pas encore un pro car je n'ai encore que 14 ans mais je compte trouver un travail dans la musique plus tard.
Au conservatoire, je pratique les percussions depuis 8 ans et la batterie depuis 3 ans. J'ai la chance de pouvoir suivre deux cursus différents : un cursus classique et un cursus jazz. J'acquiers donc de jours en jours toujours plus d'expérience , et je m'en réjouis. Je joue dans un big band, dans un orchestre d'harmonie et dans une batucada. Je suis des cours de formation musicale en classique et des cours de formation musicale centrée sur le jazz. Je passe 16h au conservatoire par semaine.

   Certaines de mes musiques sont dorénavant téléchargeables et n'oubliez pas de lire l'histoire que j'ai inventée pour "The Forgotten Crash Of Appolo 20 "en regardant les infos de la musique. J'ai également glissé des infos sur "African Marketplace". "Azote's man" n'est pas encore totalement fini.

I am an amateur composer. I mainly create MIDI music using mostly VST instruments nowadays, although I do still have my Roland JP-8000, Novation Nova and Oberheim OB-12.

More recently my son and I have invested in a Eurorack modular system and you will find some experimentations and the odd full piece here.

I sometimes create "Happy Music" although, at the moment, I appear to going through an "ambient" phase. Sometimes light, sometimes dark.

I suppose I should mention my main influences, which include Tangerine Dream, early Kraftwerk, Jean Michel Jarre, Vangelis, Ian Boddy, to name but a few. And I should thank the BBC Radiophonic Workshop for introducing me to electronic music all those years ago.

Hey folks, we're taking a break from the music for a few months.  It's been a tough slog getting to this point.  (written Aug 11 2017).  We'll be back. 

Band members:

Dave Turnbull (Vocals, Guitar, Bass, Keys, Drums)
Johannes Tschirner (Vocals, Guitar, Bass, Keys, Drums)

Our love for music creation and finding catchy hooks is of great importance. We have had many people say that we sound like a range of bands and musicians (won’t bore you with the list), but our sound can’t quite be pinpointed, which has worked in our favour.   This is the most important thing that we strive for – a uniqueness to our sound.

Our influences range through rock (of all eras), funk, soul, 70/80s keys, punk, country, from the 50s to present day, and our objective is to create songs that allow the listener to hear a story, enjoy the awesome musical aura, and experience what we have experienced, while not quite sounding like any one band that you can think of.

Technology of Silence is a Russian ambient / industrial / experimental project, existing since 2004. Founder of this project is Denis Romanov, who unites the incompatible opposites silence and music and makes it a whole, while taking a focus on the world that surrounds us and the events that take place in it, watching it from different points of view. The music of TOS is atmospheric, cinematic, melancholic and creates a certain mood. It is a fusion of ambient, industrial, IDM, minimal techno, although the band isn’t concentrating on a particular style. Environmental problems and man-made disasters are the basic themes, which draw a red line through the back-catalogue of Technology of Silence. The centre of attention in the stories of the band is a post-apocalyptic city, described as ruins of a high-tech-civilization, corrupted by mankind, and a place full of human recollections, emotions and feelings. The main context of the stories is the idea of survival in a lonely and hostile world and finding himself in life.

CORVUS "Raven constellation" is an electronic music project, wich includes Electro, Trip Hop, Alternative Dance and Dark-Ambient generes. CORVUS was founded in 2015 by Béla Mészáros (Composer, multi-instrumentalist) in Budapest, Hungary. Malwina A. Tkacz inspired Bela to actually form CORVUS. Before the foundation of CORVUS, Béla had several music projects in a wide range of genres between 2008 and 2015. CORVUS is highly infulenced by soundtracks, scores and classical music. Béla is the only official member of the group. In studio, he mostly works with female vocalists. On stage, CORVUS often performs on keyboards, electric and bass guitars. CORVUS usually mixing retro/Avant-garde styles with modern soundcapes and ideas. Since 2015, CORVUS has released two studio singles. The first debut concert was in October 2015, after releasing the first Symmetry LP. Thereafter in 2016 the second 18 EP was released in late october. In january 2017, Corvus started to recording vocals with Sherin B, female vocalist to its upcoming releases.

" Lyrics are but a reflection of the soul which is influenced simply by life" Mister M , is who I am  and   I will be releasing collections of music that have been sitting in the archives ,frozen in time. This journey has  taken me to where I am at this very moment , writing an artists Bio . Thirty seven plus years in the classroom where I made my living  working with children and young adults and loving every moment now brings me to my new adventure . I am retired  and ready to get  back to work . I always made music a part of  who I am , with the support of my family , I was able to keep it going . Music helped me get through my most stressful days and without it my life may have been much different today.  I played in a cover band once  and only once. I do love to listen and sometimes play others music but only for my own enjoyment . My love is to create ,work with other people who can identify with life as I have  experienced it, this creates a chemistry amongst who ever it is you are creating with. Its not easy to find , but if your lucky it will happen. I have worked all of my life doing what was necessary   to raise my family, that the kind of music people I surrounded myself with, they understand the privilege it was  or is to be able to get together on a Friday night  and jam. That's where the magic came from , not for money , but a simple release of creative  energy.  These people made me a better person. This first release Reset , was when it was just  Steve and myself, we get  together with our wives and children   as much as we could . When we were together Steve and would disappear and play guitars , I would record on a TEAC reel to reel   four track  . This is where it all began , we would be in trouble , with the wives you know , they wanted us to spend  more time shopping or chatting , oh well what can you do . Steve and I no matter what made it possible to write songs  and get them on tape. He and his family moved to Georgia  and that was that. Then I put an add in the paper looking for anyone interested in playing music , I stated that I played bass  and That I was interested in joining or putting together a band. That story will have to wait its my next project. I decided to release the music  Steve and I created first,  the way it is meant to be heard, frozen in time, analog format , not digital , so  appreciate it  for what it is  Music.

L’Associazione Culturale Symphonos è una libera associazione apolitica, che non si propone fini di lucro. Nasce nel 2013, dall’impegno dei suoi soci fondatori, con lo scopo di diffondere la cultura musicale nella loro città. Il suo impegno per la promozione culturale, infatti, ha radici molto antiche ed è grazie a questo sentimento di partecipazione che è riuscita negli anni ad allargare sempre più i propri orizzonti. I soci fondatori e le loro famiglie hanno da ormai 4 generazioni diffuso il proprio amore per la musica. L’Associazione è il coronamento di un sogno: poter offrire alla propria città un punto di incontro e di riferimento per quanti amino la musica e poter ampliare, così, la conoscenza della cultura musicale, letteraria ed artistica in genere, attraverso contatti fra persone, enti ed associazioni.

Formerly of Spigot, Tyro, and Toenut. Author of Advanced Genius Theory. "The Advanced Genius Theory, hatched by Jason Hartley and Britt Bergman over pizza, began as a means to explain why icons such as Lou Reed, David Bowie, and Sting seem to go from artistic brilliance in their early careers to "losing it" as they grow older. The Theory proposes that they don’t actually lose it, but rather, their work simply advances beyond our comprehension. The ramifications and departures of this argument are limitless, and so are the examples worth considering, such as George Lucas’s Jar Jar Binks, Stanley Kubrick’s fascination with coffee commercials, and the last few decades of Paul McCartney’s career. With equal doses of humor and philosophy, theorist Jason Hartley examines music, literature, sports, politics, and the very meaning of taste, presenting an entirely new way to appreciate the pop culture we love . . . and sometimes think we hate. The Advanced Genius Theory is a manifesto that takes on the least understood work by the most celebrated figures of our time."

Music Composer/producer with musicstudio located in Brussels, Belgium.

I had my musical education (starting at age 11) at the music academies of Roeselare, Kortrijk, Brugge, Aalst and Gent.  I'm a violinist and pianist with a classical education.

In formal musical life I have been member of several bands.  There lies the most of my musical experience that is still useful nowadays.

My music can be associated with experimental electro ambient trance fusion influenced by Vangelis, Jean Michel Jarre, Tangerine Dream, Pink Floyd, Air, Shostakovich.  Classical influences are never far away.

I have two older brothers who had trawled an excellent album collection  when they were young. In the evening, in bed, I was familiar with the music of Vangelis, Jean Michel Jarre, Tangerine Dream, Pink Floyd, The Doors, Janis Joplin, ELO, Pavlov's Dog, Deep Purple, David Bowie, Queen, Uriah Heep, Alice Cooper, etc ... This period was crucial to my musical development : absorbing music during my sleep.

I work as an independent composer and brought in-house my first album "The Moon has fallen into my lap" in November 2012. In the same period I released the musicvideo "What dream do you have in mind ?".

During composing I'm very often astonished that music itself sometimes forces me to go in this or that direction.  It is then as if the laws of the universe take over.

I feel very comfortable in my studio. Musicprograms such as Propellerhead Reason offer me endless possibilities to create music. My scores suit best with drama or science fiction.

Please go to my Tracks, only then the 'Reposts' disappear.

I am full owner of my work, no one else is involved.  My music can very easily be licensed.

Not too long back I met a fellow musician, a thoroughly nice chap. His name is Johnson Ramm. You know the feeling you get when you've found something new and original and you want to keep it to yourself but you can't help it and you have to shout it from the rooftops and say "This guy is amazing!!" This is one of those moments. I was asked to do some production work not long ago for his E.P. His style? Folk. Really good hearty folk. Lyrically, this guy is a genius. He writes the kind of words you wish you had thought of about 5 minutes previous! His attitude towards his work as an artist was such an inspiration as he let me guide him on certain aspects, it was me that ended up learning so much from that day. I couldn't really tell you who he sounds like, as he has a raw and unfinished quality to his voice, it just fits into place with the atmosphere that he creates from his lyrics and melodies.”

Singer-Songwriter-Elektro-Pop trifft auf sperrige Dachterrassentexte!
_____________________________________________________________________

DIE STIMME VOM DACH ist ein unabhängiges Studioprojekt von Singer/Songwriter Sten Fisher. Sten Fisher ist Musiker, Texter und Musikproduzent.

Was man sonst noch über die STIMME VOM DACH wissen sollte:
DIE STIMME VOM DACH lebt in einer kleinen Hütte aus Brettern und Teerpappe, die auf dem Flachdach eines Berliner Hochhauses steht. Am liebsten sitzt sie auf einer kleinen Mauer, lässt die Beine baumeln und beobachtet das bunte Treiben in der Tiefe. Sie liebt diesen freien und weiten Blick. Deshalb schaut sie gerne und oft auf die Stadt, ins Land und in die Welt.

Es könnte alles so schön sein. Doch die Beobachtungen der letzten Zeit beunruhigen sie.

"Was ist da unten los? Was geht da ab? Da stimmt doch etwas nicht!"

DIE STIMME VOM DACH beschließt, der Sache auf den Grund zu gehen.

BEATRICE ZANOLINI is a natural talent with a different way of making music, with new and refined interpretations: a true "vocal music", from the great classics of of Brazilian, jazz, pop and soul standards, to new compositions and extraordinary authors. She also writes lyrics (presented during concerts and recordings). Her relationship with music has been cultivated and enriched over the years through dance, even by teaching it, for over 10 years. In 2003 she released her first CD of international covers, "Aro'a nui". Since 2004, her voice joined other artists looking for new musical languages. Her album "You make me feel better" - realized with the great soccer champion Leonardo De Araujo - was released in 2007, in Italy and abroad, in over 30,000 copies; in 2008 great success of the show / concert "Canto, quindi sono” at Strehler Theatre. She has performed, among the others, at: Blue Note in Milan; Villa Arconati; Duomo of Milan; Strehler, Carcano, Sala Fontana, Litta and Manzoni Theatres; Rialto / San Gacometto in Venice; Spazio Zazie and Revel; Palazzo della Regione; the International Festival of Besana Brianza; the Vigorelli Stadium of Milan; World Join Center; Società del Giardino; Palazzo Reale; Ca' Bianca; Spazio Grassi; Castle of Inverno and many other. She has some important musical projects: the musical "Marilyn in Jazz" with the actor Fabio Bezzi and a wonderful settet (Gabriele Comeglio, Giulio Visibelli, Emilio Soana, Marco Ricci, Claudio Angeleri, Riccardo Bianchi, Marco Castiglioni); a jazz & soul quintet of excellence (WhiteBlack); an acoustic quartet (4 Friends) with Riccardo Bianchi, Giulio Visibelli and Marco Antonio Ricci; a piano and voice Duo with Marco Detto; a guitar and voice Duo with Riccardo Bianchi; the Maribè Trio with Riccardo Bianchi and Marco Antonio Ricci (doublebass); the Red Carpet Ensemble with the actor Fabio Bezzi (repertory of jazz soundtracks), playing with great musicians; she is working on a project with Paolo Pilo, guitarist and composer.
She even sang, among the others and the ones above, with Franco Cerri, Bruno de Filippi, Paolo Alderighi, Stephany Tricks, Walter Calloni, the Archimia Quartet, Larry McWilliams, Nick the Nightfly, Gianni Cazzola, Stefano Dall'Ora, Claudio Allifranchini, Attilio Zanchi, Paolo Costa, Marco Brioschi, Lele Melotti, Gilson Silveira, Fabrizio Bernasconi, Michele Franzini, Luca Garlaschelli, Antonio Fusco, Nicola Stranieri, Diego Ruvidotti, Roberto Piccolo, Alessandro Carabelli, the Soloists of Accademia delle Opere Symphony Orchestra.

Hi and thanks for taking the time to read this.  I guess Soundcloud is an ideal vehicle to demonstrate what potential I have in terms of writing music and music production.  If you listen to the tracks you'll hear a range of genres and styles which reflects the fact that I like a diverse range of music. I've also recently started making tracks in collaboration with Raine Carosin under the collective identity of Tronada - see www.soundcloud.com/tronada and with former band member Chris Summerhill and Tom Bell.  
I live in North East England and have loved to listen to and play music since my teens. Initially I taught myself acoustic guitar followed by electric guitar and bass guitar.  A few years later I played bass guitar and did the odd backing vocals in a couple of local bands, notably Hot Property.  In more recent years I took an interest in creating music electronically via midi and sequencing samples on a tracker.   I still enjoy playing "real"  instruments and have been improving on keyboards over time.   I create drum sounds by either using midi or sequencing samples on a tracker. As far as "Real"instruments go,  I have a Yamaha midi enabled Keyboard, Yamaha DDR-80 drum machine and Acoustic, Electric and Bass Guitars.   With regard to Electronic Music I sequence samples and arrange midi.  On some tracks I combine real instruments with midi or samples.   In addition I have ventured into the world of vocals too.
I record on the Boss Micro BR which is a versatile digital 4 Track digital recorder unless I am using a tracker program.  There are numerous software packages I could use but many have functionality I probably wouldn't use.  The Boss is portable and instant but I do use midi and mastering software from time to time too.
Anyway thanks for visiting my Soundcloud area and I hope you like some of the stuff I've posted here.   I did an interview with John Hodgson on the very first Teesside Band Archive Local Heroes Podcast number 1 where you can find out a bit more about me if you want to via this link  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w7JfHYEhk1Y

Founded in 1980, JDI is the only organization in the world dedicated exclusively to ending sexual abuse behind bars. JDI works to: hold government officials accountable for prisoner rape; promote public attitudes that value the dignity and safety of people in detention; and ensure that survivors of this violence get the help they need.

Contrary to popular opinion, sexual abuse in detention is preventable. Prisons and jails with committed leaders, good policies, and sound practices can keep people safe. JDI works with policymakers, advocates, and corrections officials to ensure the basic human rights of all people in detention, in the U.S. and globally. All of JDI’s work is informed by the wisdom and experiences of prisoner rape survivors.

We all read blogs and watch the videos where a fancy man in a designer T-Shirt says to find a band that you like and offer to mix their music for free to build up your portfolio. We don't really have plans to be famous or make money with music. We are merely a small family living out in the woods, in a small town, in a small state in a small region that is called New England, USA. .....that's all.

Keldari Station is a synth duo based in Denver, CO comprised of Darren D. Danahy and Kelley Donovan. 

Formed in 2012 originally as a live, all improvised instrumental project, Keldari Station prefer to make and perform their brand of electronic music by connecting together bits and bobs of analog and digital equipment, rather than exploring the depths of their personal computers and the mysteries buried there. 

Their debut EP, 2013's "Where in the Universe is Keldari Station" (released December 21, 2013) was recorded entirely live for Portugal's Dan Dada Records, and more than half of the songs on the release were written and recorded during the same week as the release.

Three of the songs from the EP, after some work and many live performances, made it onto their first studio album and CD "Brave New Worlds" (released April 25, 2015) which is where the band solidified their "Space Dub" sound which fused elements of dub reggae, psychedelia, electronic pop, and experimental music with lyrics that spoke of a change in consciousness that is either impending or already upon us, creating this "brave new world".

By the time the band had enough new material for an album at the beginning of 2016 (along with a reworking of something from the first EP) and were getting set to record, one of the bands biggest influences, the late David Bowie passed away, giving both members pause for a moment and reflection, and the decision to name the upcoming album "Say Goodbye to Ground Control" and to begin working it towards becoming a tribute to the artist. Since this point, the band has gone on to involve an outside source for the cover art (Chris Pendergraft, Torch Fire Labs) and more importantly, mixing and production assistance by Russ Sinfield (at the Chaos Cookhouse in the UK) who has in turn, began to involve other musicians outside of Keldari Station's two "core" members. 

First release from the album is the single "Lucky" which was released on an EP August 26, 2016. 

The new album, "Say Goodbye to Ground Control" is set to release late fall, 2016.

Biography:
Bradley the buyer was raised by feral wolves in Idaho. Tragedy struck when, in 2007, Bradley became severely dependent on methamphetamines, the drug of choice for the locals (being situated geographically a matter of minutes from where the Federal Government had their shoot out with local militia men on a spot called "Ruby Ridge".) Having kicked the habit, Bradley moved on to discovering religion and quickly converted to the Church of the Subgenius, having said that he felt it gave him the sense of purpose his life had always lacked. 

Shortly thereafter, Bradley began his first excursions into audio experimentation, farting into microphones and heavily processing them through tape delays, distortion, and syncing them with glitchy, digital drum beats. This produced some of the most interesting and avant garde scene music to never be heard, since Lou Reed's "Metal Machine Music". 

Soon after this, Bradley became close friends with a disheveled homeless guy near a dumpster behind Dunkin Donuts. He insisted that Bradley refer to him exclusively as "AGENT CATFACE", and thus the most musically fruitful collaboration since Lennon and McCartney was born. 

Bradley the Buyer resides in the basement. He is malnourished and addicted to benzodiazepines. He spends long hours obsessively staring into computer screens.

My musical career began in 1960 as lead singer in local Rock & Roll bands. I taught myself to play guitar, started to write songs and by 1964, my band, The D-Men, was signed up by CBS to record three 45RPM singles, featuring four of my songs. These records were successful in the Sydney charts and the group's popularity was further boosted with regular appearences on National TV, as well as tours with the Aztecs and the Easybeats. 

By 1966, my musical interests shifted towards Jazz, Blues and R&B (Soul). I was influenced by musicians such as Ray Charles, BB King, Wes Montgomery and the Soul artists who recorded for the "Stax" label. One of my demo tapes caught the attention of EMI producer David Mackay, who produced two singles for me on HMV. These records received excellent reviews. 

I had the opportunity to turn professional, when I moved to Melbourne in 1968 to join the Vibrants, a Rock band with three number one hit records. The band broke up six months later and I formed "Graduate" with two other Vibrants members, to play a diverse range of music, including Jazz, Blues, Latin and Rock. Graduate survived in various line-ups for 10 years. Often featuring a female singer out front, the band's extensive tour schedule included all Australian states, as well as six months in S.E. Asia. 

Over the years, I have shared the stage with many International acts like The Kinks, Mungo Jerry, Bee Gees, Jose Feliciano, Fairport Convention, Burl Ives and Roberta Flack. I was also in demand as a studio session musician, as well as guitarist and musical director for a number of Australia's Top Celebrities, including John Farnham, Colleen Hewett, Normie Rowe and John St. Peters. I also taught guitar for many years in music schools and my home studio. 

Some of my songs have made it into the finals of the American Song Festival (1976) and the MBAS Blues Performer Of The Year contest (1995). 

Currently I perform with *The Old Buzzards Medicine Show*, as well as a soloist on acoustic guitar.

Project Reggetiko is a musical meeting between people with very different creative roots, who share the same love for creative improvisation and direct musical interaction. The two main pillars of the musical stimuli are acoustic Reggae and Rembetiko. The idea for the project emerged when Theodore Koumartzis and Fransesco Riotta (Sise Kolombali) began jamming together, mixing rhythms and melodies that seemed foreign to each other, yet fitted together melodically. Anthony Passias and Nick Papanikoloudis joined the company in order to expand these musical horizons and take the project in new directions. Lately Sokratis Votskos have joined the project to give new approaches while Andrie Euripidou has also added vocals to some of their tracks. The result is an experimental, collective form of expression that treats music and improvisation as a way of communication between people. Our philosophy is that simple or complex, music making should always be characterized by mutual respect and honesty.

Hello, my name is Pierre. You are welcome on my Souncloud page. Listen and enjoy! Don’t hesitate to post comments. 

In my opinion, before being a technique of writing and return of sounds, music has to carry the emotion and free the imagination. My musical preferences cover a rather wide spectre. Indeed considering that the musical currents are only marks in the landscape, I do not hesitate to redraw their borders to dare improbable marriages or unexpected meetings. Rick Wakeman, Rick Emerson, Ray Manzarek, Klaus Shulze, Kraftwerk, Devo, Frank Zappa and many others else contributed to awaken my musical sensibility. Today still, they remain for me of the major references.
I like quite particularly the electronic music (EM) because, offering an infinite sound pallet, EM allows to break some proprieties, to widen horizons and to support the imagination.

My musical creations are realized and interpreted by means of  synthesizers Arturia Orgin, King Korg, Rolland Gaîa, Yamaha and various virtual synthesizers operated with Arturia Laboratory 61 and Factory 32.

Thank you for your visit.

La dinamita es un explosivo muy potente compuesto por nitroglicerina, una sustancia explosiva líquida a temperatura ambiente y muy inestable que al ser absorbida en un medio sólido (inicialmente, caparazones silíceos de diatomeas), se convierte en un explosivo más estable. La dinamita fue inventada por Alfred Nobel en 1867, sustituyendo rápidamente a la nitroglicerina para aplicaciones industriales, minería, y armamento. Desempeña un papel muy importante en trabajos como la excavación de montañas, la construcción de carreteras, demoliciones y en general cualquier obra pública que requiera el movimiento de masas rocosas.

Pronto se utilizó para el desarrollo y fabricación de ingenios bélicos, sembrando la muerte y destrucción en las zonas de conflicto. Por tal motivo, y para paliar sus efectos aunque fuera de modo simbólico, Nobel instituyó el premio que lleva su nombre expresamente referido a la Paz.

https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dinamita

Cabal Akademik is an electronic music project that features the combined efforts of Experimental IDM artists Belial Pelegrim and Beefus B.

Pelegrim programs, plays guitars, keyboards, and spends a lot of time working on sound design. Beefus is a drummer/percussionist and programmer. Both are WEATNU recording artists and released their first joint effort, WORKSHOP, in 2015. 

Cabal Akademik was formed as a way for Pelegrim & Beefus B to channel their combined passion for percussion and electronic concepts into a single, powerful sonic entity.

Odyssey is a pagan-based EP dedicated to some of the gods and goddesses of ancient Greece. It has a few different styles stemmed from the industrial genre, including rock, metal and even grunge.  If you want to hear something different and faithful, this is the EP to listen to.
Part II was released shortly after. 
Two EPS titled "Tarotbite" and "Crawlspace" were released after that.
Splintered Gypsy is currently working on the newest full-length album and finest work yet titled "Invader" to be released in 2017.

Yukke Roswenda Heckmann, better known as YUCCA ROSE, is a leading Indonesian Smooth Jazz and World Music vocalist / lyricist and well respected contemporary painter from Malang in East Java.

Over the last eleven years, she performed with a wide variety of jazz bands / solo artists and recorded two albums with her Jakarta based orchestra “Major Seventh” (the self titled "Major Seventh" debut album and the second album named "Eastern Sunrise" - both published by DiscTarra Indonesia). She released her first solo album "Tree of Life" in March of 2013 and the second album "Radio Dalam Orchestra - Wir haven Spass" in 2016. All albums and two single releases feature some of the greatest Indonesian jazz performers and include collaborations with European Jazz and World Music artists.

She is produced by her husband, the German musician and audio engineer Peter Heckmann (Hakeem Luqman) and now divides her time between Indonesia and Germany.

As a highly regarded contemporary painter and designer, Yucca Rose still finds the time to paint - constantly adding to her extensive collection of artwork. Additionally, she creates larger scale wall murals, unique bamboo toys and wood sculptures and adds her colorful painting style to recycled wood boxes, wardrobes and tea-containers in her Rumah Kreatif workshop in Indonesia.

NOTABLE APPEARANCES:
Nine Muses Club, Jakarta 2007

(plus many more appearances throughout Southeast Asia in 2013 and 2014)

Yucca Rose also appeared in a leading role as actress, vocalist and announcer in the Cirque Du Soleil style theatrical show “Regalia - The Enchanted Forest” (developed by Raining Heart Productions) at the Bali Theater (Bali Safari and Marine Park) with stunning live performances on May 14th, 2011 and the Gala on June 4th, 2011. For this show, she is also credited as Costume / Stage Designer and Artistic Co-Director.

Magma Brothers is an electronic music duo consisting of Felix Guerra Jr. (FLIXXER) and Xavier Garrido (Shakezilla). They are both from Rio Grande City, Texas and are a multi-genre producing group and djs that are open minded to all types of music. Artists that influenced Magma Brothers are Deadmau5, Keys n Krates, A-Track, Diplo, Skrillex, Robin Schulz and many more.  Magma Brothers have played at local bars in Mcallen, Texas to playing at house parties for friends and have opened for Caked Up, EDX, and Speaker of the House.  They have many tracks to produce of all genres and many shows to perform. Magma Brothers believes in having a good time with positive attitudes but is also a very professional and creative group. Each original track or mix is made with heart and soul that is center to our philosophy of being artists. Their main goal and passion involves listening, making, and playing music. Music is what drives them to grow as artists and inspires them to make music.

In the city of fort Collins, He started as a Drummer at around age 11. Did some drum tracking for a FOCO based bands EP, Amzyr (FIND-THEM-ON Spotify,Itunes,Pandora, ETC.) After moving metal band to rock to indie, to folk, he decided to go solo and revert back to his high school, middle school days where he dabbled in producing on a laptop w. FL studio. Soon upgraded to Reason, (Similar program) and began composing songs from scratch, also taught himself guitar, piano, and basically mimicking live acoustic instruments like drums and guitar and doing them digitally on a keyboard. Does sometimes sample from my drums or guitar. Authenticity is what he prides himself in. Pure music but also simple and meaningful enough for people to dig. Music can be meaningless and still have depth and purity. Music has no boundaries! He has always worked jobs to support himself while supplementing his music "Hobby" on the side and feels he has put in the time in learning instruments, engineering, mixing, mastering, etc. to now feel confidant to start pushing his music and gifts out their! He produces 90% of his beats, using no samples unless they are samples recorded himself, and a very likable artist! Enjoy

Thanks for all of the recent follows, comments, likes and reposts. I am doing my best to check out your music also, comment, like, follow and repost in many cases. I like artists being creative in any way they can, so forgive my wide range of reposts. I grew up on 60's and 70's Rock, Pop, Classic Rock, Psychedelic and Fusion Music. A number of Rock and original Rock bands followed. I also played regular gigs as part of a duo with a flute player (one of my best for life friends, Ed). Of course, we did a bunch of Tull songs as well as Classic Rock and originals with the duo and in our bands. Before and during my college Music Education, I had taken up Classical Guitar. That was during the day. At night I was playing in a Disco Band. In later years, I reunited with Ed, and formed a Tull tribute band. A number of years later, I was playing Pedal Steel Guitar and guitar in an all original band (Thunderegg) that had a number of nice gigs in Connecticut and New York City. Over the past 10-15 years, I've been focusing on writing and recording original music. Due to my background, I am spread over quite a few genres and many times that is driven by a collaborator. I have been collaborating with a lot of great people. I'm one of 3 Bobs who formed an internet band called 3bobrock. We tend to pull from a Pink Floyd sound and other sources for our original music. My most recent regular collaborations are with Jennifer Foss, a wonderful singer of many styles who also has a lot of great ideas as a cowriter. Several of our recent songs are favorites on our Soundcloud pages. Jen and I are looking forward to writing and recording much more together. Another collaborator who I have a growing number of tracks with is Briand Melonson (Bamtone). We tend to aim for Alternative Rock and some Americana. I am also always working on creating music for possible film, tv and advertising use. Therefore, among the tracks you find on my pages will be some shorter instrumental cues. My "New Tracks" Album page is where I put new favorites. Some of my tracks are available for purchase and download. You are always welcome to stream and listen for free here. Finally, my website, bobporrimusic.com., may be of interest to you. I'm a full time musician, songwriter, and guitar instructor. There is a good deal of free material (video guitar instruction, scales, chords, jam tracks etc.) on my website. I appreciate any interest, comments, emails etc. I am also am a Guitar Coach for the Guitar Tricks website with a number of online "classes" each week. Bob Porri

I'm a Uruguayan musician. I play the drums and compose my own music with software tools into free and privative plattforms.
Recently, I added a Nord Lead 2X synthesizer, a KORG TR-rack module and Roland TD4KX electronic drums to my set.
The style relates with the electronic genera, more exactly, with the ambient, space, synth, world music, chill out, industrial and experimental sub-genera.
I hope that you enjoy the music of the same way as I enjoyed on having done it.

Sincerely.

SIROK.

His interest for the music world begun when he was a very small child, showing good sensibility and musical taste, with a sonorous perception of universal quality.
Nevertheless, it was in his adolescence when he began his learning of drum with his teacher, Gastón Buenseñor, who gave to him the technical basic tools to continue with his formation of a self-taught way.
During his path he penetrated into diverse interpretive styles: Rock and roll; Afro; Candombe, Jazz, Progressive, Pop and more beat styles.
The contribution as a drummer in his musical projects never restricted to the merely interpretive thing, but he took part always of the rhythmic and harmonic arrangements; choirs and voices.
Today, Alfredo is an electronic music composer (in a wide sense), so as a drummer as by making, composing and programming music with synthesizer.
"Spaceghost" (2006), "Experimentation" (2008) and "Event horizon" (2013) are his first Independently produced discs of original Electronic music. These discs clearly distinguish the artist's evolution in his capacity as a producer, composer and musician, from the first job so far.
In addition, he takes part as co-author in such projects as " 4 Seasons" (2008) and "Solar system" (2009), together with the Uruguayan composer Marcelo Sartorio, shaping the group in silico DUO.
SIROK needs your help as a fan, financially or through a media opportunity, to project his music as an ultimate lifestyle.
All SIROK music are registered (AGADU - Biblioteca Nacional).

I have had classical piano lessons since I was a very very small girl. My mother was an opera singer, & her mother played every night as the "music entertainment" @ what is now known as a bed & breakfast. It was then known as a boarding house.  All three of us kids started lessons around the age of three or four.  My brother stills plays beautifully.  

Growing up, we moved many many times.  One of the greatest solaces of my life both then & now is my absolute love of music. All kinds of music interests me, & I will try to play them all on the piano.

Focusing hard live improv sets with weekly/daily open mics, Devecseri (Adam Dev) aims to innovate musical performances with technology. A focus on live remixing, virtual instrument substitution for productions and improvisational techniques has led Devecseri to a live workflow that supports musical freedom and sound manipulation insanity without the traditional DJ setup.

Devecseri released his 'Lux' EP in August of 2016, a mangled journey of genres straying from electronic to jazz, classical, arabic, downtempo, ambient, vaporwave and more. A video for the title track 'Lux' was released in March 2017 as well as a remix EP standing on it's own, which features a remaster and 5 different artist's interpretations of the piece.

Update: 

I've been trying to write songs using a conventional DAW set-up for some months now and it has been interesting and challenging. However, progress has been deathly slow largely because I don't have a lot of spare time to sit at a desk and fiddle with wires and a mouse.  With hindsight, I realise I would have been much better off focusing on writing with my phone while using the DAW for additional development/mixing etc at a later stage, instead of trying to start songs with a computer.  I'm happy with that approach - so that's what I'm now going to do.

About the clocktoys: me plus occasional others (but usually just me). I have written songs from a tender age and never let the hysterical laughter grind me down (well, not often). I taught myself to play keyboards with the mighty Casio VL 1 perched on top of my little sister's toy organ (the old asthmatic wheezing kind made from elastic bands, glue and the cheapest plastics known to man).
I enjoy the creative freedom of writing alone and my music is, frankly, a muddle of influences veering off in different directions. Which is a good thing in my book.
As well as my music I may also eventually get round to reading some short stories (do i hear a a low murmur of pleasure at the back?). Basically, I'll be boring the arse off you in as many different ways as I can think of.
I like: music from many different styles past and present but in my writing I often look back to classic indie music like: the smiths; aztec camera; cocteau twins; the associates; badly drawn boy; new order; teardrop explodes; japan; early omd; echo and the bunnymen
I wish: i could play the guitar like Johnny Marr; sing better
Visuals...
Any talented amateurs interested in making short videos to interpret my tracks? (Not with me in them, I hasten to add). If so, why not get in touch?
If you've read all the way down to here, can I please say a little thank you, embrace you in a manly way, and ask that you keep listening. One day I'll get it right!

My music is essentially a soundtrack to my thoughts, musical poems that are part classical, part electronic, somewhat minimalist, purely digital, and rather odd.

I have been composing since I was about 16 years old without any proper musical education, using mostly just MIDI and nothing else, only very recently have I switched to more modern tools. What I always tried to accomplish was an electronic music that feels live, coming from places and times beyond ours.

You can use my music freely for non-commercial purposes, or really however you want if you're an indie artist or a vlogger without money to spare. Just please let me know when you do so and mention me in the credits. If you wish for me to make more music, you can buy some of my better tracks on my Bandcamp for however much you're willing to pay at https://sphericrezonance.bandcamp.com/ (and get the rights to use them commercially if you are a company or some serious professional). You can also simply donate anything you wish to my PayPal at astrologon@gmail.com - just click here: https://t.co/mB2e4MXCQX.

I am open to composing commissioned soundtracks for multimedia projects, just be aware that I am a citizen of the Czech Republic.

To everyone listening to my music, I would like to say thank you, as I am truly grateful that you have taken time out of your day to find and listen to my music. I am also grateful for any and all reposts, comments, follows, and likes I have and will continue to receive.

I don’t have a recording contract, or any big name endorsements. My songs aren’t even on the radio, yet. All I am is just someone who sits in front of his computer and records music before posting his creations online for the world to hear.

As well as being influenced by the ancient Celtic culture in which I grew up and descended from,  I have also been influenced by my early childhood in Liverpool up to the age of 7; the city that produced the Beatles and many other world-class musicians and other talents.Then experiencing the rest of my childhood in the west country from  aged 6 to 15 being surrounded by the ancient history which influenced me.  Having traveled worked and volunteered in various other countries has also influenced my music and my life; resulting in my interest in many genres such as country, rock, folk, jazz, and blues leading to world music. Der Sound der alienmindbenders

Trommelfellzermürbende Beats prasseln auf loungige Jazzclubatmo. Die ALIENMINDBENDERS sind mal düster, mal romantisch, dann wieder zynisch zuckend oder elaboriert funky. Der Geist des Projekts ist in etwa so schwer zu greifen wie das Wesen einer Frau: mal ist sie die skrupellose Femme fatale, die dir in einem Moment den Rücken zeigt und im anderen mit ihren verträumten Kulleraugen dein Herz zerfließen lässt. Mal lässt sie dich mit Gehirnzerfetzenden Beats strammstehen und dann wieder dahin gleiten wie auf Schäfchenwolken. 

AMB ist die Liebe zum musikalischen Detail, zum Zitat der Postmoderne, die Faszination der auffordernd dunkeln Leichtigkeit, mit der janeBO ihre Songs einsingt. Das Ergebnis: das Album ALIENATION. Ein Wortspiel, ein erster Einblick in den außerterrestrischen Kosmos jenseits der Vernunft und hin zu den Ursprüngen des Gedankens: dem gefühlsbetonten Ich, dem der Zutritt zum Paradies aber seit Menschwerdung verwährt bleibt. So dreht das Alien seine Kreise, ständig in Wartestellung, zwischen Überich und Es bleibt eigentlich nur eine Chance: Mensch Leute, the true sound is out there - get out on the dancefloor and believe!

description:
Composer of instrumental music, with a preference for longer, progressive and complexely arranged pieces with lots of instruments.   

Have played guitar for 30+ years, but I am probably a slightly odd type of guitarist. Not particularily interested in the guitar genre, not too keen on listening to long solos, etc. I don't enjoy playing for people - a party-killer, in short. 

However, leave me alone with this wonderful tool (or the keyboard, which I play too), and I will start experimenting with it, searching for something to develop. 

Strongly interested in classical music and anything remotely related to that. I want to construct music with a similar structure and complexity, although with other instruments, and in my own way...  
___________________________________________________________

During 2010-2013, I worked on a suite of related pieces, GUITARS PLAYED BY DS, with every sound played on the electric guitar. A major undertaking, and (all-in-all) 45+ minutes long, all complexely related and released in five segments.

During 2014-early 2015, the main focus was on an 'epic', the LONG INSTRUMENTAL, a progressive work with lots of different instruments and sounds, restless and complex. Recorded dark evenings, nights, and early mornings ...  Some sections stand on their own feets and can represent the longer work: QUARANTINE, MYSTERY, and FANFARE. 

The 2014-2015 recordings also resulted in two shorter pieces: CAMBRIAN EXPLOSION and CLUSTER OF WARNINGS.

During 2015 I initiated a suite played on classical guitars - GUITAR STRUCTURES. It is a series of slowly changing ideas, a weave of melodies and harmony, the first section out in April 2015 (the 2nd came 2 years later).  

I played guitars on Tolubai's wonderful ambient piece 'MEMORIES' (August 2015).

EARTHSHINE came out in January 2016; a darker and slightly dissonant progressive piece.

SILENCE out 1st July 2016.

IGNITION out in September, with TOLUBAI. LET THERE BE LIGHT out 22th Sept 2016, with PuppyWolf. 

20/11-2016: The OORT CLOUD PROJECT I-IX. An 18+ minutes long progressive synth-based instrumental, with lots of short guitar phrases integrated; related to the track Ignition. Took a year to record, a massive piece, based on variations on 2 themes from the first two minutes. Also, the spinoff PASSAGE was released. 

GROTESQUE released too in the end of 2016. The 19th January 2017, I released a draft version of OMMA CONTRAPUNCTUS PROJECT - to be completed one day. The 4th February 2017, the track '3 WORLDS COLLIDE' was released.

'Guitar Structure No. 2' out in March 2017.

WORK IN PROGRESS/PLANNED: 'Best of 2 worlds', '3rd Guitar Structure' but unknown when they are ready... It is likely that something else appear first. 

___________________________________________________________
Many thanks for visiting here, and for the comments, 'Likes' & reposts.
