Michael McKay Combs is a Veteran Singer songwriter who has played with many big names in the country and rock industry! Joining his first band at the age of 15, Combs took to the stage like an immediate pro! He fronted many rock bands early in his career and landed a development deal with a major label in 2003. After the band fell apart Combs moved to Nashville after graduating college and begin paying dues in the country world. While in Nashville Combs accomplished many things and landed a small publishing deal. Making many TV appearances and recording with some big name producers, Combs was well on his way to making a big name for himself. However, Combs mother would fall ill and after his last deal fell through, he returned back to KY. After a couple years out of the spot light, Combs begin writing again and is making a big comeback. The future is now looking up again for Combs and he doesnt plan on stopping any time soon. 

BIO By Randy Smith-Music industry press

I am a collaborative lyricist/singer/songwriter who has been working with various artists from abroad & near for 8 yrs here on soundcloud and its been quite an experience that will carry on for the years to come. I started out very early as a light opera singer and again very late as a contemporary singer working within the Electronic Underground Scene in primarily Europe. My first band was one other artist who was a Minimal Darkwave/Synthpop composer from Belgium named Frank Reynders of Devil Shy in whom I wrote with for approx 1 year in 2011. We released an album in 2012 that had some success and we released a couple of videos on YouTube. Thereafter I started working with 2  artists whom I had met here on soundcloud, Stephen Surreal of UNUNE who is a Dark Ambient/Dark Media composer in which I did primarily spoken word for him as well as an another Belgian Dark Minimal/Industrial artist. This is when I was approached by more & more artists. In 2014 I met Gary Watts of Nature Of Wires and to make a long story short this is where it all began to unfold with tons of airplay over various internet radio stations to some more undergrounds physical radio stations such as The BBC in Herefordshire UK which was a regional station. We then released "Cyber Rendezvous" in 2016 which had great success in most of Europe. In 2015 prior to the physical album release, one of the tracks entitled " Perfect Menagerie" was No 5 on the Top 30 Pop Charts in most of Europe on SOL Radio stationed in Israel-A program with Oren Amram & "Synthesize Me". We have since then in 2017 released a digital remix album of all the  original tracks from the physical release simply entitled "Cyber Rendezvous Remixed". We have aalso released 3 official videos on YouTube for the tracks entitled "Perfect Menagerie", "Dance With Your Own Skeletons" (remixed by Lloyd Price of Massive Ego)& "we Kill All" (remixed by Cosmo of My Cosmo). I have also released my own Collaborative work independently on Bandcamp as well as a physical release of a 9 track album entitled "Collaborations Vol. 1" by CountessM in 2015 which also had some viral success. There have been misc digital releases of my collaborative work with such artists as In This Mode, Denovomutans, DROID SECTOR DECAY  and many other artists.

I am open to a limited amount of collaborations these days for a reasonable & affordable flat fee as of February 9th 2017 for aspiring Electronic artists & composers whom are serious about the music industry.

Daft Punk - for their creative, inventive and raw electronic sound that inspired generations of people all over the world.

Amycanbe hail from Cervia, Italy. Originally comprised of Marco Trinchillo and Mattia Mercuriali, they formed in 2002, but actually started as a quartet in 2005, after Francesca Amati and Paolo Gradari joined. After the first live performances in clubs, theatres and local bars, Amycanbe record a self-produced demo (Yellow Suit - EP). The debut album Being A Grown-Up Sure Is Complicated is released in October 2007, produced by Mario Thaler. After three years of intense gigs around Italy and England, the EP called The World Is Round, born from a translation & interpretation project of Gertrude Stein’s novel, is finally out on 25th May 2011.

From late October 2011, the second album Mountain Whales is out and the line-up is extended with the arrival of guitarist Glauco Salvo. During 2014, with several dates and tours around Italy, the line-up is reduced again to a four-piece, this time with the entry of a new musician, as well as producer of the new album, Mattia “Matta” Dallara. The third album of Amycanbe, Wolf, is out spring 2015.

Lewisland is a solo project created by Nigerian born-Italian based Indie Pop Artist, Rapper, Singer-Songwriter, Blues Rocker and Multi-Instrumentalist Lewis Angelo. Lewisland aims at producing well crafted melodic songs with lyrics that reflect on the everyday struggle, lost love and acts of bravery.

Lewis was born in Lagos, Nigeria and now resides in Italy. Already at a young age Lewis was influenced by artists his parents listened to like Barry White, Lionel Richie, Diana Ross, Phil Collins, Michael Bolton and Kenny G. 
Lewis states that the music culture in Nigeria limited his way of thinking and seeing music in general. "Nigeria is a beautiful country but she unfortunately has a poor taste for Rock, Jazz, Blues and many other music Genre, So moving to Italy was a total boost to my Song Writing and Composition" Quotes Lewis.
As a teenager my gift for melody came through  listening to bands such as Westlife, Backstreet Boys, Avril, Shaina Twain, The Corrs, Bryan Adams and The Goo Goo Dolls. These artists helped me build a strong foundation for a more mature style of music and Song Writing. 
I started playing the piano when I was 7 yrs old. While still taking piano lessons, I grew more interested in trying out other musical instruments! At age 14 I got my first Acoustic guitar, and later I passed on to the drums and the bass guitar. And I started writing songs at age 15.

Bands that influence me are: The Goo Goo Dolls, Lenny Kravitz, Ben Harper, Prince, Splender, Edwin McCain, Norah Jones, John Mayer, Jack Johnson, Kem, Smokey Robinson, Doobie Brothers, Chance The Rapper, Anderson .Pakk, Childish Gambino, J. Cole, Incognito, Anita Baker, Lallah Hathaway, Donny Hathaway, Simply Red, The Isley Brothers, Tina Turner, Stereophonics, Mr. Big, Creed, Savage Garden, Mint Condition, Richie Kotzen, Craig David, Howie Day, Sixpence None The Richer, Alex Band (The Calling), John Waite, Kings Of Convenience, Richard Marx, Eric Martin, Hall & Oates, Tears For Fears, Oasis, Keane, Needtobreathe, Nickelback, 3 Doors Down, The Corrs, Vanessa Carlton, Ryan Adams, Staind, Dave Matthews Band, Five For Fighting and many others :)

Long story short- My name is John, I a 4x years old.Without finding a vocalist, I am the sound behind Wet Luci. All music recorded in my tiny studio office mostly at odd hours of the night. My instrument of choice is guitar. I do all of the guitar on my songs and some of the bass. I also do keys on the few songs that I decide to lay piano on. I use edrums for convienence and because I cannot keep a beat. I have a 2001 PRS Custom 24 as my only electric. I tried over the past year adding a 2nd electric-1st a prs se245. Gorgeous but sucked. Then a Dano 12 string semi hollow. Sucked. So sticking with just my PRS and my Takimine Acoustic Electric G30 series. I use a small Blackstar amp to feed into my daw, Donner mini pedals, Studio One for DAW, 192 Audio Interface, Digimax optical pre-amp, and studio monitor. Akai midi keys, Squire Jaquar Bass and some brand of mics that I do not use.I pump out as many songs as I can (as the saying goes, throw shit against the wall until 1 turd sticks. ) I am hoping to lure in a gullible singer as I do write decent lyrics and I do not feel my songs are complete without vocals. Never been on stage legally but I want to make that accomplishment.

New EP 'Grind' is being completed. We have decided to go in a new direction and focus strictly on a Blues Rock direction with less manipulation and a straight forward 3 or 4 track song with heavy focus on guitar. At this point we do not want to keep putting out music without a vocalist even if it is just for one EP as a side project for someone or different vocalists for each song. We started this idea late in life (mid-forties) so limited time to get our stuff heard. Not in it for money or career change, I just want to say my stuff was played on .....

Wet Luci came to be in the summer of 2016 in Irving, Tx.  Our 1st LP -NOVEMBER while lacking any vocals was released and distributed in October 2016 along with  the 1st single from the LP, SHALLOW.

The 2nd LP 'Until the Bitter End' was completely in January. 
  
  
Wet Luci is a mix of Metal, Alt-Metal, Grove Metal, Experimental, and Fusion Jazz. Many of the songs were recording in one take, or at least one or tracks on the song.

About the Artist
Joe Fusco is a composer and multi-instrumentalist whose primary instrument is guitar. He grew up in the Philadelphia area and he began doing session work at some of the city’s major recording studios while he was still in his teens. Although a rocker at heart, he quickly sharpened his R&B skills when it became obvious to him that most of the session-work in Philly revolved around R&B music.
During that period he recorded with many R&B legends and worked on Rock, Fusion, Jazz, Folk and Celtic projects as well.

For the past several years he’s been focusing on creating music for acoustic finger-style guitar and loving it! … Dream Number 7 is his first offering in this genre and it spans a wide range of styles. From modern to traditional, from Roots and Americana to Folk and Celtic, his music reflects the natural beauty of the countryside that he loves, the places he’s been, the people he’s met and the life that he’s lived.

Hey guys! We are back!
Yes, a little different, true, but with the same love for music and rock. However, in order for you to understand the changes that have taken place, let's go back in time and unravel some of our trajectory here.
Well, it all began unpretentiously in 2011, when our bass player, Alexandre, sought to dive into the ocean of music and practice on his instrument. In this environment of study and improvement, he met two of our members: Mr. Nunes (classmate in the music theory class) and Dayvid (the teacher). Moved by the same passion - music, they decided to meet outside the school so they could practice their learning and have fun together. They invited Theo, our first drummer, Alexandre's uncle, to join the group and Pedro, step-son of Alexandre, for the role of vocalist and guitarist.
From there the play developed and the compositions began to be born. However, when Pedro decided to move to Canada in 2015, we decided to record the songs that we had, before his departure, so that they would not be lost in time and so we could listen to them wherever we wanted. We recorded the songs, in an amateur way and with the resources that we had until then, and created our SoundCloud. And, to our grateful surprise, it was a success! (Yes, for us, who did not expect the reach and the positive reviews we got, it was a great success!).
Faced with all this, our motivation only grew. We decided to start the composition of our second album. However, we were embezzled, without vocalist / guitarist and without drummer, due to health problems of our dear Theo. The solution was to invite Lilian, Pedro's mother and Alexandre's wife, to take on the vocals. Besides her, Roger, guitarist and music producer, also joined the band. Finally, Leo Bruno, drummer and friend of the band, took the hit. And here we are again!
We would like to thank all of you who support our music. All the suggestions and constructive criticisms have been and will always be heard and, in this new album, we try to put all this learning into practice. Obviously, with all the changes that have taken place, our sonority has also been modified, considering the varied musical influences of our members. But one thing is certain: rock will always be in our veins and music in our hearts.
Thank you for all support!

MIJA Biography

Born and raised in a musician family from Gothenburg in Sweden, her father was a well-reputed musician in a famous Swedish band between the sixties and eighties.
Mija started in a school-choir when she was 14 years old, and began to take song lessons for a song coach for several years. At this time she also started her first rock band with her own music. They played together for some years and had a lot of gigs during that time. At the same time she joined an established gospel-choir for ten years and during this time they did approx twice gig in a week in which Mija often was the song soloist. They also made an album.

Later she joined another funk-rock band, LC-Band with professional studio musicians. In this band she stayed for a couple of years before they dissolved and they released two singles and they were doing gigs from time to time.  At the age of 22 she went to study a musical program at a folk high school for  
2 years. She continued to take classical/jazz/pop vocal lessons and was a member of the vocal ensemble on the school. The ensemble gave performances in classical, musicals and folk music. After finishing this education Mija applied for and was accepted to University for music in Gothenburg. But turned it down and began to work as song/music teacher for six years on and off and during that time she also supported herself as a singer in a song duo (jazz, folk music and blues). Mija was also hired as cafe singer at two different restaurants for several years. She continued to support herself as a singer. During this time Mija sang in 1 cover band, 1 jazz-quartet, and continued with her own song duo, worked as a studio singer and participated in some well-known musicals and was also hired as a background singer for other artists.

1998 she got a roll in a bigger production of the musical Jesus Christ Superstar in corporation with Baltic Republic. She played Maria Magdalena. During these years Mija still continued to singing with different bands. Following year she became a singer in a cover band called Lazy Babes in which Magnus Rosen from Hammerfall also played. She sang with them for a couple of years. Later she started a new band, Robberband with studio musicians from the Swedish rock and pop elite and they did a lot of gigs together. Nowadays Robberband includes members from Lost Horizon, Nostrademus etc.  And they are still doing gigs at clubs, parties etc.
Mija has supported herself as a singer in many different bands, with all styles. She has made approx 3000 gigs & 300 studio sessions. The latest project is the co-operation between Mija and Benny Jansson (Tears Of Anger, Ride The Sky, XSavior).
Mija and Benny found each other musically and began to write songs together in 2006/2007. A new member, Hasse Nilsson, a drummer [Dimension Zero, Gaffla Knivur, Diabolique] has also joined the band in 2008. The rest of the band is session musicians from different well-known projects.  
And more to come.....

Hello! My name is Hans Henning Thomas. I think, I´m more a soundengineer than a songwriter and more a songwriter than really a singer/musician. I started to play guitar  late, i.e. on the age of sixteen and had never learned an instrument before. So my first musical influences have been by songwriters, because I firstly payed most of my attention to the lyrics. My musical understanding developed at this time, moving away from home and hanging around with some friends. At this time I did my first steps by grounding a band. But we were influenced more by the era of such as the Doors, Rory Gallagher, Neil Young, Jimmy Hendrix,  Pink Floyd or the first Deep Purple cast, - while the actual successful music at this time sadly was New German Wave and the like.

Later, after becoming an firstly unemployed physics, I followed my intention and turned my passion to trade, becoming a sound engineer. After all I got a well paid job in an public supported analog sound studio for a decade, recording and teaching some people in sound engineering. Some of my songs, published here, are a result from this era.

Now I´m working again as a physics / engineer, and music became my fervour again. In my life I lived in many different towns, in East and West Germany -  i.e. Düsseldorf, Braunschweig, Paderborn, Berlin, (1/2 year Tropea, Calabria, Italy), Hagen Westf, Siegburg, Dresden (Neustadt) and now I turned to Rahden, Westf., again, where I live deep in the country in an integral nature reserve. The experiences, I got and the people I met, might be an insperation for my philosophy and my music.

Thanks to the new computer technologies, I was able to build myself a modern home recording studio again, to produce my own and my friends music in a good quality.

My intention for the next time is, to listen to the theme and sound of the nature and turn it to music. The Intro of my song "Wild Ducks Flying" ("Flieg mit dem Wind") is a good example for this project. It came up to me, when I recorded some wild ducks trough my open window, flying over my house. I loaded the samples into a software synthesizer and started to made music to it, leaning on the style of some early Pink Floyd projects. This song should be regarded to migrant birds in analogy to the human society, nowadays.

I plan to go on this way in my next holiday, at least for a month, recording and using the sounds of a forest at night and the like. 

I hope you listen to, like and enjoy at least some of my songs ;-)

About Atertrip:
We were born in 2012, in Modena. 
The working line-up is: Greta Salvalai (singer), Tommaso Marchesini (guitar), Federico Salvarani (bass), Eleonora Ricci (keyboards), Federico Bedostri (drums). 
When we're asked what our genre is, we get quite anxious, because we never know how to answer, but you could probably say we work in the neighbourhood of AlternativeRock/PostProgressive music. We set for ourselves the goal to evolve with each new song we compose. 
We've always been more oriented towards live performance, but lately we've discovered how fun it is to record/edit/mix/compose with the computer, so everything you hear here is made by the five (inexperienced) of us in every step of the way! :)

2A at the Playground is a producer/musician playing 'dusty' electronic music. Dusty like an old vinyl playing dirty drums, warped guitars and analogue sounds. Our influences? Led Zep, Pink Floyd, Jimi, Beastie boys, Chemical brothers, Deadmau5.

Exploring the realms of electronic music.

I started out using Caustic, the Android music creation tool and I still use it occasionally from time to time.  I moved onto Ableton Live Lite 8,  the 'I, Improvised 3' project inspired an album created with one take recording which can be found on my Bandcamp page.

It has limitations I thought were too crippling to create full songs but you just need to be a bit creative.  True it's a compromise but it goes to show you can still make music even with these software limitations. 

I've since moved onto using Mulab 6 and more recently Usine Hollyhock II which isn't like a traditional DAW, it's more aimed at live performance.  It is incredibly powerful with a wealth of samplers, granulators, glitch tools, groove machines and physics engines.  It's also a totally modular environment. 

As well as synthesizing sounds, field recordings or found sounds hold a particular fascination in the way they can capture a unique moment  resulting in sounds that cannot be synthesized. 

The tools in Hollyhock allow me to dissect these sounds, making them non-linear which kind of takes them outside of time to give a different perspective.

When you first play Robert’s music not only do you hear it but see it. Big Cities at the dead of night, not a soul around, just neon and streetlights. An enchanted forest where mythical creatures live. Robert creates music that hits all your senses with its harmonic vocals, brooding, undulating baselines and pulsating drumbeats.
But how does he do it? How does he take instruments’ and musical styles that usually don’t play together and make them work?
Robert began listening to music in the mid 80’s, but it really took a hold in the 90’s when Rap, Trip Hop, Grunge and Electronic music all came into their own, and Robert drank them all in. Having started his musical career playing drums in local bands in the West Midlands, Robert packed up and moved to North London for a life behind the mixing desk. There he has worked on his own unique sound, an “ellisonsound”.
So take a trip to the dark side with him... “are you ready” for it? 
He thinks you are.

Windmill are from Liverpool and the band in its present form met six months ago, they all discovered they loved the likes of Joan Baez, Angus and Julia Stone, Neil Young, Brian Wilson, Beck, Leonard Cohen, Simon and Garfunkel and the Velvet Underground. 

Birdman was their first single written by guitarist/songwriter Mick Dolan and produced by Yorkie for Universal Shoes Productions; it was recorded at Yorkie’s House Of Light studios in Liverpool.
It gained extensive radio airplay from Chris Currie, Dave Monks, Tom Robinson, Simon Raymonde, John Kennedy, Gary Crowley, Tracey Hedges and Alex Huskisson. 
It was one of Janice Long’s and Tom Robinson’s favourite tracks and they both said it is ‘a hauntingly beautiful song, an amazing track full of atmosphere’.

I am Stan Magendanz & I love listening to & creating Ambient, Dark Ambient & Experimental music. I have no professional aspirations - I just really like creating music / manipulating sounds. It's my way of relaxing after a hard day at the office. Most of the time, I can't be bothered setting up my studio monitors so nearly all my tracks are produced using monitoring headphones (Sennheiser HD 280 Pro). 

Nearly all tracks are downloadable and covered by a Creative Commons license. Collaborations / Remixes are welcome so feel free to experiment - no need to get my permission first. Just send me a link to your track when you're done :)

To the artists I follow; I do my best to try to listen to as many of your tracks as possible each night (I listen to each track all the way through - you went through the effort to create a track so you deserve to have it heard in full). If I miss a recent upload of yours, please forgive me...

Thank you for taking the time to visit my little corner of the soundcloud.

Jesús Lastra aka Jalastram/Flat Stone is a Madrid-based self-taught artist from Maracaibo, Venezuela. He began to experiment with audio editing software in 2007. Then, he started composing ambient music, or more specifically, soundscape, drone and experimental music within the electronic genre. Lastra has been part of Naviar Records Label since 2014.
 
Also, he has designed sound effects and music for video games, and has a library with more than 1.000 own sounds under the license of Creative Commons. In 2015, as inspired by photography, he decided to test image editing software by using the glitch style. Thanks to his perseverance and his remarkable talent, he has been part of Glitch Artists Collective since 2015.
 
Jesús is a passionate artist open to share and create art with people around the world. He is always eager to share and exchange new knowledge.

We both love to make music.  However, recording songs that noone else can hear is not as much fun as creating something others maybe like as well. We met by accident when Carina recorded some songs with her new band (that was my old band) in my homestudio. Some years later, in 2012, when Carina's new band had become her old band, we decided to write and record music together. JuneMay was born. This is all about the fun of recording our own songs.

In July 2017 we released our first album through Spotify, Amazon, iTunes... It contains the best songs from our first 3 packages of 10 songs (January - March). All songs have been remixed, remasterd and partly rearranged. 

Until today we recorded three complete sets of 10 songs each ("January", "February" and "March"- ok not very creative ;-) which would have been called "albums" years ago. We have completed recording the vocals for our fourth collection "April" and are in the process of arranging and mixing the songs (roughtly one per month...).

Sunstrings was formed in 2012 by singer-guitarist Takuya Matsuda and drummer Saya. They're noted for their simple, direct melodies, and bold sound you wouldn't expect from a duo.

The band's name is a portmanteau of "sun" and "strings." Also, the Japanese pronunciation of the English word "sun" is the same as that of the Japanese number 3, so the name Sunstrings is also understood as meaning "3 strings."
The band chose this name in reference to Takuya's 3-string guitar and the simple melodies that form the basis of their songwriting.

The duo are influenced by 80s indie rock and 70s punk rock. In August of 2015, Sunstrings celebrated their third year as a band by releasing their first album, Green. They released the follow-up album, Orange, in September of the same year.

Gunz aka Reese Spratley was born on July 25 1985 in Suffolk Virginia and lived in the rough section of the city called Saratoga. Eventually he moved to a town called Windsor and then Smithfield where he found his passion to sing. In January 1999 at the age of 14 while in a math class,he had a little time on his hands and started writing rap lyrics. He started recording during the summer and came up with the alias Babyblue. In 2000 he released a mixtape called "Babyblue On Loccdown" and his peers were impressed. In 2002 as a sophmore in high school, him and a friend formed a group called the High Rollerz and changed his name to Nightryder. The mixtapes kept coming and coming then he changed his name to Ryder Gunz. Eventually the High Rollerz would split and Gunz decided to go solo and thats when everything took off. He took a break until 08 when he came out with the album "The Execution" which featured the song Crip Thang which established a buzz among his peers and locals. Since then hes put out banger after banger to take his music national and now ready to take thing worldwide.

Michael Storey Jr a.k.a. The Wordologist is a native Nashvillian actor, martial artist, singer, and writer of screenplays, songs, spoken word, and conscious rap lyrics. He has been writing both songs and poetry since age 15, and was a member of several local R&B groups in his area, and has performed for many years at various venues ranging from coffee houses, to political conventions, to concerts opening up for artists like Anthony Hamilton and Angie Stone. Michael is an avid follower of his own self created philosophy, the Quadratic Principle, which means to live one's life within the proper balance of spirituality, family, career, and recreation. Michael is a "freelance philosopher" who is always seeking new and old knowledge on an endless quest to acquire multitudes of wisdom. This is the philosophy/ideology that Michael chooses to reflect all throughout his poems and songs. "My biggest dream, aside from being the greatest father to my children and the greatest King to my Queen, is to bring REAL lyricism back into mainstream music, and to put out material that is clever and creative enough to entertain the listeners, but more importantly, to push people to think beyond the parameters of coptic thought, thus sparking an evolution in the entire human collective. I know this dream is not yet a reality, but with endless time and dedication, it CAN be. Amen, Ashe, Hotep and Namaste!"

I'm a jazz guitarist, composer and recordist. I also teach jazz at the University Of The Pacific and Consumnes River College. I own two recording studios - Studio Bohemia a large tracking facility and Art House Sound, where I do mixing and mastering out of my home. My band is The Henry Robinett Group, which has been in existence in one form or another since 1985. We released 4 CDs.  The latest, "I Have Known Mountains" is the 5th in the aeries but without the group. I also play with The Capital Jazz Project.  In addition I'm active in producing various artists across the stylistic spectrum. 

I've taken a lot of my inspiration from my late cousin,  jazz great Charles Mingus. I lived and studied with him briefly in the mid-late 70s.

On this site I will put things up, all unfinished works in progress, unless I indicate otherwise, to either show what I'm working on or to give an overview.  We're working on a couple of CDs.  There's a wide variety of material, so I don't know whether it will become two or three different CDs, straight ahead jazz, my more accessible material or what. Many of the pieces here I have no plans to release on a CD. But it's good to get some feedback or just a feel for what folks are listening to. 

On another note, as I'm sure there's enough music here to upset everybody. Part of the pleasure of being a guitarist who plays jazz is being exposed to a wide variety of music in the popular idiom.  And frankly I love all genres. Part of my uniqueness is being willing and able to play at most styles.  I don't consider my more "accessible" elements selling out, because I really like them, and I still play everything in my own style, rather than trying to cop anyone else either compositionally or guitaristically. What's more what personally drives me crazy is the narrow minded, musical fascism; almost a form of musical bigotry, that an artist has to stay within the confines defined as X or that anything but X is invalid as an art form worthy of ones attention.  The timbre of guitar and music has changed over the years. I like to explore it all. 

I believe part of an artists responsibility to is write what he hears and play what he imagines, if he likes it, regardless of other peoples considerations or pressure, one way or the other. If I only did straight ahead jazz or only did funk or only rock, I'd be dishonest.

Born and raised in Stockton, California, Antonio Roccucci was bitten by the bug of electronic music in his early years of high school. After years of only being a listener, he decided it was time to take his love for his music to the next level. From a plastic, two-deck mix controller, Antonio has adapted to all kinds of musical interfaces such as digitalism and turntablism. After years of practice, he has been able to be a part of Stockton's growing PLUR scene and has teamed up with other Stockton native DJs such as: DJ Shaun Ente, DJ Joe Q, DJ Alán, DJ MC, Audio Climaxx (Frank Gallardo) and Codec (Joel Vasquez).
